divs: Sighting DetailsFriend called and told us to look in the western sky to see if we could see what they were seeing. They were about ten miles southeast of us. We could see a light that was much bigger than the brightest stars just hanging in the sky. It was drifting slowly to the west-northwest horizon. It was going the opposite direction of just about everything in the sky that night. It was too big to be a satellite and did not have any FAA regulated lights indicating it was a plane. Unlikely to be military as it was too close to the regular landing lanes of authorized aircraft.
Summary: Bright Floating Light in Western Sky
